cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper presents a method for improving the classic RANSAC algorithm for robust optimization in computer vision tasks using neural guidance. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training neural networks to optimize an arbitrary task loss, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves optimization and robust estimation, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on various computer vision tasks, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics).
